<br>
The only way i've been able to get a group in PoV so far was to get a group through the trials and then bring them to PoV.  I think the stigma of mages being an underpowered class for several expansions (besides our uber - now gimped beyond any real usefulness t-rods) will take a while to get past.<br>
<br>
For the majority of players out there, cle/tank and SLOW are viewed as &quot;must have&quot; for any effective group.  DPS wise, monk, rogue, wiz are still viewed by most as more desireable than mages.  Even if we can outdamage every class in the game in an exp group besides rogues, it will take some time for that to sink in.<br>
<br>
So losing any effective means of soloing hurts the mage class a lot, especially since a very large portion of the mage community gained most of their exp solo previously.<br>
<br>
I don't think that slow fits our class, even if it were from pet procc'ing weapons.  It would step on other class's toes too much.<br>
<br>
Maybe some nice parses and sustained DPS figures are what we really need at this point.  If I can get a groups in PoP, I really wouldn't miss soloing at all.  It was nice to have the option when groups weren't available though.<br>
