ed). No puller? No problem. I just wear my extend range ring and go pull. I use my spell Eye of Tallon to its full capacity and scout out monsters to pull, it helps and keeps me from getting jumped. I always try to form a group from available manpower. I consider my greatest asset is that I can work with anyone no matter what class they play. No chanters? A bard will do just fine (most people probably don't know that a good bard can mez/charm almost as well as a chanter). No tank? Aego Jabober, DS him up a bit, put all available buffs and let him tank or if worse comes to worse grab a ranger. Although our pets are not as tough as a real warrior, but none the less a tank is a tank. Sometimes you can't just form the perfect &quot;ideal&quot; xp group and gotta work with what you got on hand. <p><p><a
